In a call with President Ali Abdallah Saleh of Yemen, John Brennan, a representative of the United States, expressed the willingness of the United States to assist the Yemeni Government and people in their fight against al-Qa’ida in the Arabian Peninsula. Brennan stressed the importance of close cooperation in counterterrorism efforts and the ongoing investigation of recent events. He also commended the efforts of Yemeni security forces in battling al-Qa'ida terrorists regularly. Additionally, Brennan mentioned that international partners, including the U.K. and Saudi Arabia, are prepared to support the development of a more stable and prosperous Yemen, which would undermine al-Qa’ida’s activities in the country.